  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to the house where my mother's other sister was, her sister Lily, and my great-grandmother, Granny Klock, and my mother's-- mother's sister, in other words, my mother's Aunt [?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Rae, ?] Rachel.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her name was Italeander, which is Dutch for Italian, because her husband's parents had come from Italy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I arrived at my-- thinking my grandmother's house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was my Granny Klock there, my great-grandmother, my mother's other sister Lily, her husband and her two children, and my Auntie [?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Rae ?], who was a widow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that was a happy/sad occasion for me to arrive back there alone to England, where I had come and I'd been with my sister as a child on so many occasions.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always had terribly happy memories for me, places where my aunts and uncles always bought me presents, and my grandmother always bought me clothes, English clothes, where with-- which were then good-- the best you could get in the world.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it was a place of happy memories for me on this terrible, sad time when I got there, terrible.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As far as I knew then, and know now, my mother was still in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know what happened to my Auntie Annie or my cousin John at that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[SIGHS] My uncle, my uncle, my-- Sam, my mother's eldest brother, thought I should go to school because I hadn't been really to proper school for many years.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his son, whose name is the same as mine, he was going to a private school, and my uncle thought that maybe he should send me to the same school.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, I went for two terms to this school in the Hampstead Garden Suburb in London-- it's a well-known area in London-- with a very little English.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
